results.occurrenceRemarks: Conservation status; Vulnerable. Largest (in terms of body size) member of the panthera species found in Africa. Globally, it's the second largest (In terms of body size) panthera after the Tiger. Males grow a mane (it's believed the darker the mane the higher the testosterone levels), while females lack the mane. Male lions have a larger bulky body compared to the females (lioness) whom are lighter & agile. This attribute gives the females an advantage during hunting....In my national country language, adult lions are called "Simba" while cubs are called, "Shibli". In my native kamba language, they are called "Munyambu"...
